 196:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) The PVD is used to monitor the VDD power supply by comparing it to a 
 197:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           threshold selected by the PVD Level (PLS[2:0] bits in the PWR_CR).
 198:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) A PVDO flag is available to indicate if VDD/VDDA is higher or lower 
 199:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           than the PVD threshold. This event is internally connected to the EXTI 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccK7S6kH.s 			page 6


 200:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           line16 and can generate an interrupt if enabled through the EXTI registers.
 201:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) The PVD is stopped in Standby mode.
 202:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 203:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** @endverbatim
