 331:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** /** @defgroup PWR_Group4 Main and Backup Regulators configuration functions
 332:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *  @brief   Main and Backup Regulators configuration functions 
 333:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccK7S6kH.s 			page 10


 334:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** @verbatim   
 335:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****  ===============================================================================
 336:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           ##### Main and Backup Regulators configuration functions #####
 337:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****  ===============================================================================  
 338:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****     [..]
 339:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) The backup domain includes 4 Kbytes of backup SRAM accessible only from 
 340:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           the CPU, and address in 32-bit, 16-bit or 8-bit mode. Its content is 
 341:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           retained even in Standby or VBAT mode when the low power backup regulator
 342:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           is enabled. It can be considered as an internal EEPROM when VBAT is 
 343:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           always present. You can use the PWR_BackupRegulatorCmd() function to 
 344:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           enable the low power backup regulator and use the PWR_GetFlagStatus
 345:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (PWR_FLAG_BRR) to check if it is ready or not. 
 346:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 347:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) When the backup domain is supplied by VDD (analog switch connected to VDD) 
 348:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           the backup SRAM is powered from VDD which replaces the VBAT power supply to 
 349:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           save battery life.
 350:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 351:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) The backup SRAM is not mass erased by an tamper event. It is read 
 352:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           protected to prevent confidential data, such as cryptographic private 
 353:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           key, from being accessed. The backup SRAM can be erased only through 
 354:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           the Flash interface when a protection level change from level 1 to 
 355:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           level 0 is requested. 
 356:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       -@- Refer to the description of Read protection (RDP) in the reference manual.
 357:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 358:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) The main internal regulator can be configured to have a tradeoff between 
 359:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           performance and power consumption when the device does not operate at 
 360:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           the maximum frequency. 
 361:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) For STM32F405xx/407xx and STM32F415xx/417xx  Devices, the regulator can be     
 362:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           configured on the fly through PWR_MainRegulatorModeConfig() function which  
 363:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           configure VOS bit in PWR_CR register:
 364:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) When this bit is set (Regulator voltage output Scale 1 mode selected) 
 365:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              the System frequency can go up to 168 MHz. 
 366:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) When this bit is reset (Regulator voltage output Scale 2 mode selected) 
 367:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              the System frequency can go up to 144 MHz.
 368:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              
 369:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****        (+) For STM32F42xxx/43xxx Devices, the regulator can be configured through    
 370:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            PWR_MainRegulatorModeConfig() function which configure VOS[1:0] bits in
 371:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            PWR_CR register:  
 372:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            which configure VOS[1:0] bits in PWR_CR register: 
 373:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) When VOS[1:0] = 11 (Regulator voltage output Scale 1 mode selected) 
 374:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              the System frequency can go up to 168 MHz. 
 375:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) When VOS[1:0] = 10 (Regulator voltage output Scale 2 mode selected) 
 376:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              the System frequency can go up to 144 MHz.  
 377:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) When VOS[1:0] = 01 (Regulator voltage output Scale 3 mode selected) 
 378:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              the System frequency can go up to 120 MHz. 
 379:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                           
 380:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****        (+) For STM32F42xxx/43xxx Devices, the scale can be modified only when the PLL 
 381:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            is OFF and the HSI or HSE clock source is selected as system clock. 
 382:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            The new value programmed is active only when the PLL is ON.
 383:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            When the PLL is OFF, the voltage scale 3 is automatically selected. 
 384:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         Refer to the datasheets for more details.
 385:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         
 386:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****        (+) For STM32F42xxx/43xxx Devices, in Run mode: the main regulator has
 387:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            2 operating modes available:
 388:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) Normal mode: The CPU and core logic operate at maximum frequency at a given 
 389:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              voltage scaling (scale 1, scale 2 or scale 3)
 390:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) Over-drive mode: This mode allows the CPU and the core logic to operate at a 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccK7S6kH.s 			page 11


 391:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****             higher frequency than the normal mode for a given voltage scaling (scale 1,  
 392:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****             scale 2 or scale 3). This mode is enabled through PWR_OverDriveCmd() function and
 393:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****             PWR_OverDriveSWCmd() function, to enter or exit from Over-drive mode please follow 
 394:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****             the sequence described in Reference manual.
 395:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              
 396:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****        (+) For STM32F42xxx/43xxx Devices, in Stop mode: the main regulator or low power regulator 
 397:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            supplies a low power voltage to the 1.2V domain, thus preserving the content of register
 398:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            and internal SRAM. 2 operating modes are available:
 399:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****          (++) Normal mode: the 1.2V domain is preserved in nominal leakage mode. This mode is only 
 400:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****               available when the main regulator or the low power regulator is used in Scale 3 or 
 401:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****               low voltage mode.
 402:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****          (++) Under-drive mode: the 1.2V domain is preserved in reduced leakage mode. This mode is 
 403:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****               available when the main regulator or the low power regulator is in low voltage mode.
 404:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****               This mode is enabled through PWR_UnderDriveCmd() function.
 405:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****             
 406:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** @endverbatim
