 674:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** /** @defgroup PWR_Group6 Low Power modes configuration functions
 675:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *  @brief   Low Power modes configuration functions 
 676:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *
 677:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** @verbatim   
 678:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****  ===============================================================================
 679:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****               ##### Low Power modes configuration functions #####
 680:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****  ===============================================================================  
 681:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****     [..]
 682:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       The devices feature 3 low-power modes:
 683:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Sleep mode: Cortex-M4 core stopped, peripherals kept running.
 684:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Stop mode: all clocks are stopped, regulator running, regulator 
 685:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           in low power mode
 686:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Standby mode: 1.2V domain powered off.
 687:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    
 688:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    *** Sleep mode ***
 689:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    ==================
 690:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****     [..]
 691:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Entry:
 692:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) The Sleep mode is entered by using the __WFI() or __WFE() functions.
 693:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Exit:
 694:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) Any peripheral interrupt acknowledged by the nested vectored interrupt 
 695:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              controller (NVIC) can wake up the device from Sleep mode.
 696:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 697:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    *** Stop mode ***
 698:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    =================
 699:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****     [..]
 700:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       In Stop mode, all clocks in the 1.2V domain are stopped, the PLL, the HSI,
 701:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       and the HSE RC oscillators are disabled. Internal SRAM and register contents 
 702:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       are preserved.
 703:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       The voltage regulator can be configured either in normal or low-power mode.
 704:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       To minimize the consumption In Stop mode, FLASH can be powered off before 
 705:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       entering the Stop mode. It can be switched on again by software after exiting 
 706:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       the Stop mode using the PWR_FlashPowerDownCmd() function. 
 707:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    
 708:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Entry:
 709:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) The Stop mode is entered using the PWR_EnterSTOPMode(PWR_MainRegulator_ON) 
 710:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              function with:
 711:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Main regulator ON.
 712:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Low Power regulator ON.
 713:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Exit:
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccK7S6kH.s 			page 20


 714:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) Any EXTI Line (Internal or External) configured in Interrupt/Event mode.
 715:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       
 716:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    *** Standby mode ***
 717:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    ====================
 718:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****     [..]
 719:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       The Standby mode allows to achieve the lowest power consumption. It is based 
 720:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       on the Cortex-M4 deepsleep mode, with the voltage regulator disabled. 
 721:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       The 1.2V domain is consequently powered off. The PLL, the HSI oscillator and 
 722:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       the HSE oscillator are also switched off. SRAM and register contents are lost 
 723:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       except for the RTC registers, RTC backup registers, backup SRAM and Standby 
 724:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       circuitry.
 725:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    
 726:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       The voltage regulator is OFF.
 727:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       
 728:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Entry:
 729:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) The Standby mode is entered using the PWR_EnterSTANDBYMode() function.
 730:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (+) Exit:
 731:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) WKUP pin rising edge, RTC alarm (Alarm A and Alarm B), RTC wakeup,
 732:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              tamper event, time-stamp event, external reset in NRST pin, IWDG reset.              
 733:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 734:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    *** Auto-wakeup (AWU) from low-power mode ***
 735:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    =============================================
 736:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****     [..]
 737:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       The MCU can be woken up from low-power mode by an RTC Alarm event, an RTC 
 738:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       Wakeup event, a tamper event, a time-stamp event, or a comparator event, 
 739:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       without depending on an external interrupt (Auto-wakeup mode).
 740:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 741:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (#) RTC auto-wakeup (AWU) from the Stop mode
 742:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****        
 743:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) To wake up from the Stop mode with an RTC alarm event, it is necessary to:
 744:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the EXTI Line 17 to be sensitive to rising edges (Interrupt 
 745:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 or Event modes) using the EXTI_Init() function.
 746:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Enable the RTC Alarm Interrupt using the RTC_ITConfig() function
 747:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the RTC to generate the RTC alarm using the RTC_SetAlarm() 
 748:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 and RTC_AlarmCmd() functions.
 749:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) To wake up from the Stop mode with an RTC Tamper or time stamp event, it 
 750:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              is necessary to:
 751:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the EXTI Line 21 to be sensitive to rising edges (Interrupt 
 752:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 or Event modes) using the EXTI_Init() function.
 753:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Enable the RTC Tamper or time stamp Interrupt using the RTC_ITConfig() 
 754:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 function
 755:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the RTC to detect the tamper or time stamp event using the
 756:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 RTC_TimeStampConfig(), RTC_TamperTriggerConfig() and RTC_TamperCmd()
 757:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 functions.
 758:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) To wake up from the Stop mode with an RTC WakeUp event, it is necessary to:
 759:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            (+++) Configure the EXTI Line 22 to be sensitive to rising edges (Interrupt 
 760:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                  or Event modes) using the EXTI_Init() function.
 761:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            (+++) Enable the RTC WakeUp Interrupt using the RTC_ITConfig() function
 762:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****            (+++) Configure the RTC to generate the RTC WakeUp event using the RTC_WakeUpClockConfig
 763:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                  RTC_SetWakeUpCounter() and RTC_WakeUpCmd() functions.
 764:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
 765:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****       (#) RTC auto-wakeup (AWU) from the Standby mode
 766:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****    
 767:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) To wake up from the Standby mode with an RTC alarm event, it is necessary to:
 768:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Enable the RTC Alarm Interrupt using the RTC_ITConfig() function
 769:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the RTC to generate the RTC alarm using the RTC_SetAlarm() 
 770:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 and RTC_AlarmCmd() functions.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\asus\AppData\Local\Temp\ccK7S6kH.s 			page 21


 771:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) To wake up from the Standby mode with an RTC Tamper or time stamp event, it 
 772:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****              is necessary to:
 773:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Enable the RTC Tamper or time stamp Interrupt using the RTC_ITConfig() 
 774:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 function
 775:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the RTC to detect the tamper or time stamp event using the
 776:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 RTC_TimeStampConfig(), RTC_TamperTriggerConfig() and RTC_TamperCmd()
 777:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 functions.
 778:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****         (++) To wake up from the Standby mode with an RTC WakeUp event, it is necessary to:
 779:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Enable the RTC WakeUp Interrupt using the RTC_ITConfig() function
 780:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****           (+++) Configure the RTC to generate the RTC WakeUp event using the RTC_WakeUpClockConfig(
 781:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****                 RTC_SetWakeUpCounter() and RTC_WakeUpCmd() functions.
 782:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** 
