 953:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c **** /**
 954:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   * @brief  Checks whether the specified PWR flag is set or not.
 955:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   * @param  PWR_FLAG: specifies the flag to check.
 956:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *          This parameter can be one of the following values:
 957:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_WU: Wake Up flag. This flag indicates that a wakeup event 
 958:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  was received from the WKUP pin or from the RTC alarm (Alarm A 
 959:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  or Alarm B), RTC Tamper event, RTC TimeStamp event or RTC Wakeup.
 960:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  An additional wakeup event is detected if the WKUP pin is enabled 
 961:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  (by setting the EWUP bit) when the WKUP pin level is already high.  
 962:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_SB: StandBy flag. This flag indicates that the system was
 963:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  resumed from StandBy mode.    
 964:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_PVDO: PVD Output. This flag is valid only if PVD is enabled 
 965:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  by the PWR_PVDCmd() function. The PVD is stopped by Standby mode 
 966:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  For this reason, this bit is equal to 0 after Standby or reset
 967:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  until the PVDE bit is set.
 968:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_BRR: Backup regulator ready flag. This bit is not reset 
 969:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  when the device wakes up from Standby mode or by a system reset 
 970:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                  or power reset.  
 971:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_VOSRDY: This flag indicates that the Regulator voltage 
 972:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                 scaling output selection is ready.
 973:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_ODRDY: This flag indicates that the Over-drive mode
 974:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                 is ready (STM32F42xxx/43xxx devices) 
 975:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_ODSWRDY: This flag indicates that the Over-drive mode
 976:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                 switching is ready (STM32F42xxx/43xxx devices) 
 977:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *            @arg PWR_FLAG_UDRDY: This flag indicates that the Under-drive mode
 978:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   *                 is enabled in Stop mode (STM32F42xxx/43xxx devices)
 979:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   * @retval The new state of PWR_FLAG (SET or RESET).
 980:Lib/StdPeriphs/src/stm32f4xx_pwr.c ****   */
